[{"role":"system","content":"\nUseful to know:\n"},{"role":"user","content":"Instructions: hello world console app in c#"},{"role":"user","content":"Specification: Here is a simple Hello World console application written in C#:\n\n```csharp\nusing System;\n\nclass Program\n{\n    static void Main()\n    {\n        Console.WriteLine(\"Hello World!\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\nExplanation:\n\n1. `using System;` - This is a using directive that brings the System namespace into scope. This namespace contains the `Console` class.\n\n2. `class Program` - This is a declaration of a new class. A class is a container for methods and data related to those methods.\n\n3. `static void Main()` - This is the Main method of the class. This is the entry point for the application.\n\n4. `Console.WriteLine(\"Hello World!\");` - This is a method provided by the Console class in the System namespace. It prints the string given as a parameter to the console. In this case, \"Hello World!\" will be printed."},{"role":"assistant","content":"That's correct. Note that the `Main` method is a special type of function in C#. Every executable program must contain a Main method somewhere in one of its classes. The Main method is the first method to be executed when a program starts."}]